thumb|drawing of a rikka arrangement   is a form of ikebana ; the term came to be a popular synonym for ikebana in the 15th century , when rikka became a distinctive element of interior decoration in the reception rooms at the residences of the military leaders , nobility , and priests of the time .

flower arranging : chrysanthemums represented waterfalls in the 15 ' arrangements of rikka , a type of this japanese art form

